**Customer Success Manager

The Customer Success Manager role builds upon the foundation of the Junior Customer Success role.

>I am a confident, secure member of the Octopus CSM Team with a proven record of excellent customer engagement.


***Core Competencies
- I meet our NRR, GRR and CSAT targets across my entire book of business.
- I confidently communicate with my book of business, effectively engaging with customers via the methods that they prefer
- I understand the importance of customer lifetime value and focus on strategies for customer retention alongside growth.
- I own customer satisfaction with high-level client management
- I use customer engagement metrics to inform my strategy and improve customer experiences.
- I seek to understand the real needs of my customers, and I am comfortable selecting the best approach to best serve those needs (including saying no).
- I am proficient with my tools and the core duties of a Customer Success Manager
- I confidently know when and how to effectively engage with the wider Revenue Organisation (e.g. Support, Sales and TAM) to best serve my customers  
- I confidently anticipate my customer's needs. I am effective at asking leading questions to help lead the customer to the solution.
- I am excellent at prioritising my workload.
- I am quick to recognise when I need help, and I know how to do this in an effective and timely manner.


***Personal Growth and Leadership
- People tend to ask me for my opinion when making decisions because I have a proven track record of making wise choices.
- I am fuelling the team's desire to learn, by mentoring, running brown-bag sessions or sharing useful videos/blogs/papers.
- I can manage difficult conversations and tactfully challenge others, leaving them with a positive impression of myself and Octopus.
- I am a confident and proficient teacher of my craft.
- I am devoted to learning; it's become a natural part of my life.
- I can confidently step outside my comfort zone and adapt quickly to unfamiliar areas of Octopus.
- I am actively introspective and take time to work on my personal and professional development.
- I happily take responsibility for my own mistakes and I learn from the mistakes of others.
- I am proficient in handling difficult conversations, always working towards positive outcomes.

***Team Collaboration & Attitude
- I add value to my team by being a trusted, proactive supporter of my team and its leadership, and by delivering high-quality work with a minimum of fuss.
- I recognise problems early and get in and fix them regardless of whose fault it is.
- I am good at recognising problems outside the scope of my work and eagerly get involved in improving our product, our environment, and our processes.
- I happily tackle all problems regardless of difficulty.
- Every venture has mundane tasks, I'm the one who can be trusted to get them done and get them done right, usually with a handful of ingenuity.
- I recognise and accept that change is constant, and my approach allows me to tactfully challenge, or confidently adapt, depending on which I deem appropriate.
- I possess writing skills that let me be clear, concise, articulate, and persuasive in all of my outgoing communications.
- I balance customer needs and team goals, maintaining a data-driven approach.
